  "instructions": [
    "Heat olive oil and butter in a heavy‑bottom pot over medium heat until melted and slightly browned.",
    "Add diced onion and sauté until translucent, about 4 minutes.",
    "Stir in minced garlic, cumin, coriander, and paprika, cooking for 1 minute until fragrant.",
    "Pour in cooked chickpeas, capers, and broth, bringing the mixture to a gentle simmer.",
    "Reduce heat to low, cover, and let the tagine steam for 20 minutes to meld flavors.",
    "Uncover, stir, and cook uncovered for an additional 5 minutes to thicken slightly.",
    "Taste and season with salt and black pepper to preference.",
    "Garnish with fresh cilantro before serving hot."
